# Frontend Core Rules (myvoice-fe)

- Use TypeScript strict-safe patterns. Avoid `any`; if unavoidable, isolate and document why.
- Keep presentational components in `src/components` and page-level composition in `src/pages`.
- Reusable state belongs in Redux slices (`src/store/*Slice.ts`); avoid duplicating API/loading/error logic in pages.
- Centralize HTTP access through shared utilities and slices; do not scatter `fetch` implementations across unrelated components.
- Handle async UI states explicitly: loading, empty, error, and success.
- For forms, keep controlled inputs and validate before dispatching async thunks.
- Do not store sensitive data in localStorage; auth/session tokens must be handled in the current app-approved mechanism.
- Keep accessibility basics: meaningful `alt`, button semantics, keyboard-focusable interactions.
- Prefer small, composable components/hooks over very large page files.
- Before finishing changes, run `npm run lint` (and `npm run build` for risky refactors) when possible.
